5. **State Formation**: Over time, some of these savannah societies evolved into complex states or empires, characterized by centralized political authority, bureaucracies, and standing armies. Examples include the Mali Empire (circa 1230 – 1600 CE), which controlled vast territories across West Africa, and the Kanem-Bornu Empire in Central Africa (800–1894 CE).

