5. **Infrastructure**: Colonial powers often built infrastructure (roads, railways, ports) primarily to facilitate resource extraction or their own administrative control. After independence, this infrastructure might not align perfectly with the needs of the new nation, yet it can be challenging and costly to alter or replace.

