   - In frequentist statistics, parameters are considered random variables with a known distribution (often normal or t-distribution), and observations are treated as realizations of these random variables.
   
   - Frequentists focus on hypothesis testing, where they set up null hypotheses, choose significance levels (like 0.05), and determine whether to reject or fail to reject the null based on observed data.

