Cuba, officially known as the Republic of Cuba, is an archipelago located in the Antilles, spanning over 110,000 square kilometers with a population of more than 11 million. Its capital is Havana (La Habana). The country enjoys a subtropical climate year-round, fostering fertile agricultural lands where sugarcane is the primary export commodity. Cuba boasts architectural gems like the San Carlos de la Cabaña Fortress, Havana Vieja, Malecón, and Torreón de Santa Dorotea de Luna de la Chorrera. The island's pristine beaches are popular for relaxation, while its waters offer excellent scuba diving opportunities due to vibrant coral reefs.

