In "The Lie of the Discipline of Symbolic Logic," John Michael Kuczynski critiques the contemporary academic approach to teaching symbolic logic within universities. The author, a former professor and tutor, argues that this discipline is not genuine logic but rather a bureaucratic practice masquerading as intellectual rigor.

